{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And every day we had this counting business.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was hot in the summer, and it was cold in the winter, and it was raining, and snowing, and it was hailing, and it was slush.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I've been back to Belsen several times-- once in the winter, and-- and-- when it was slush.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was in my warm overcoat, and the wind was whistling across the heathland there in Belsen, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I felt drained and cold after five minutes out there, just like that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How we survived in those days, with the limited clothes that we had, I never know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I guess we just got used to it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that was a big ordeal every day to have this appel and the counting.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When that was finished, we had the first meal of the day, as they called it, which was brown liquid, which they said was coffee-- ersatz-coffee, imitation coffee.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was brown, and it was liquid, and it was warm, that's all you could say for it, really.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's all we had in the morning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Nothing else-- no bread, or corn flakes, or milk, or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At lunch time, we had turnip soup.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had a mug full of turnip soup.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We'd all have to queue up, and somebody would dish out the soup.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In our case, it was my brother Rudy, the entrepreneur.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was in charge of dishing out the food, you see.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He'd wrangled his way in there, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I'm hesitant to saying all these kind of things, because in a way, Rudy ought to tell better the story, himself.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
